The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Corporate Briefs
																								 Birla Corporation has reported a turnover of Rs 455.83 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2007, compared with Rs 417.06 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The operating profit jumped to Rs 159.73 crore from Rs 103.16 crore. The profit after tax rose 53 per cent to Rs 103.13 crore from Rs 67.54 crore in the year-ago period. The earning per share increased to Rs 13.39 from Rs 8.77.																								 Graphite India Ltd has registered a 22 per cent rise in sales at Rs 277.99 crore for the quarter ended September 2007 compared with R																								 the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The net profit for the quarter rose 38 per cent to Rs 37.95 crore from 27.43 crore in the year-ago period. 																								 Century Plyboards has reported a consolidated turnover of Rs 239.03 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007, against Rs 182.68 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The consolidated profit rose to Rs 36.11 crore from Rs 30.15 crore in the year-ago period. 																								 Ceat Ltd has reported a net profit of Rs 25.50 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2007, against Rs 3.83 crore in the same period last year. The companys gross sales rose 8 per cent to Rs 649 crore from Rs 602 crore in the year-ago period. Exports grew 31% during the period.																								 Usha Martin Limited has posted a 50 per cent rise in profit before tax at Rs 62.28 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007 compared with Rs 41.47 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The profit after tax rose 49 per cent to Rs 45.95 crore from Rs 30.89 crore in the year-ago period.																								 Berger Paints has recorded a 9.5 per cent rise in net sales at Rs 320 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007, from Rs 350 crore in the year-ago period. the profit after tax rose 15.5 per cent to Rs 32 crore from Rs 27.7 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. 																								 Srei Infrastructure Finance Ltd has recorded an 80 per cent jump in its consolidated profit after tax at Rs 56.5 crore for the half year ended September 30, 2007, against Rs 31.31 crore in the year-ago period. The profit before tax rose to Rs 63.6 crore from Rs 44.98 crore in the corresponding half-year period last year.																								 Ramsarup Industries has reported a 22 per cent growth in total income at Rs 331.96 crore for the quarter ended September 30, 2007, compared with Rs 272.12 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The operating profit rose 94.27 per cent to Rs 35.61 crore compared with Rs 18.33 crore in the year-ago period. ADVERTISEMENT
